                                                                                                               Sport Briefs
                                                Thakur appointed manager   Dharamsala: Anurag Thakur, president of the Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association, was Tuesday appointed the manager of Indian cricket team for Champions Trophy commencing in South Africa from September 22.  Thakur, a former Himachal Pradesh skipper, had earlier worked as manager of Indian team for the Under-19 World Cup, a HPCA statement said.  Asif route  Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has decided to send pacer Mohammed Asif to South Africa for the upcoming Champions Trophy via London, while rest of the squad will travel via Dubai. The PCB has taken the decision to avoid any untoward situation that may arise if Asif arrives in the city.  Day-long fast  Coimbatore: Around 100 cricketers of various clubs affiliated to Coimbatore District Cricket Association (CDCA), Tuesday observed day-long fast to protest the irregularities in CDCA rsquo;s working, blaming office-bearers for ldquo;doing nothing rdquo; to develop the game. The protesters belong to 21 out of a total of 36 clubs affiliated to the district-level body.  Diego worry  Milan: Under-pressure Argentina coach Diego Maradona has checked into a clinic in northern Italy in a bid to lose weight, his personal doctor said on Tuesday. ldquo;Maradona travelled to Italy to check into a spa he knows where he will do a diet to lose five kilos, rdquo; his personal doctor Alfredo Cahe was quoted as saying in Buenos Aires.  EPL rule  London: English top flight clubs will have their squads limited to 25 next season with eight players having to be lsquo;home-grown rsquo;, the Premier League said on Tuesday. It said the 20 clubs had agreed the change, effective from the start of the 2010/2011 campaign. ldquo;The definition of home grown is trained for three years under the age of 21 by somebody in the English and Welsh professional system, rdquo; chief executive Peter Scudamore said.  BNR in semis  Gangtok: City club BNR thrashed Tata Football Academy 5-2 to storm into the semi-final of 31st All India Governor rsquo;s Gold Cup football tournament at the Paljor Stadium Tuesday.  CWG meetings  New Delhi: Rattled by the criticism of the capital rsquo;s tardy preparations for the 2010 Commonwealth Games, sports minister M.S. Gill Tuesday held hectic meetings with Delhi chief minister Sheila Dikshit and Indian Olympic Association president Suresh Kalmadi to take stock of the situation.  Boxer death  London: Darren Sutherland, who won an Olympic bronze medal in boxing at last year rsquo;s Beijing Games, has been found dead at his home, manager Frank Maloney said on Tuesday. He was 27. Sutherland was found hanged at his home Monday by Maloney.  AGENCIES
                                                                                                                                                                 
